	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>January 5th 5624</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>113 Canal Street 2nd floor</placeName></p>
			<pb n="Envelope"/>
				<p><addressee>Revnd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
				<p><placeName>371 Walnut <sic>street</sic></placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>January 5&#44; 1864</date>.</p>
				<p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaac Lesser</addressee></sic>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Very honored sir&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Herewith you will receive &#36;6. Please send me a set<lb/> of pentateuchs with English translation&#44; which were printed in <placeName>Ger&#45;<lb/>many</placeName>.  I hope you will remember that the &#36;6. was the price you set<lb/> for it when you were last here.  I shall be very much indebted to<lb/> you if you will send me these as early as tomorrow per express&#44; be&#45;<lb/>cause the buyer will stay here for only several days.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please enclose a prospectus of the works which you<lb/> are now printing for &#36;5. as well as a catalogue of all your works&#44;<lb/> for today there is a meeting in my community with regard to organi&#45;<lb/>sing a Sunday school and I may be able to dispose of some of your<lb/> things.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With every respect&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>113 Canal Street</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>2nd floor</placeName></p>
		</body>
